{
  "texts": [
    "For example, if the exam questions or similar variants are publicly available and, thus, may be present in the training data, the LLM does not demonstrate any knowledge outside of training data memorization.",
    "122 In fact, these types of tests can be misleading in estimating the model's true abilities in terms of comprehension or analytical skills.",
    "Many studies have reported limitations in the output related to comprehensiveness, safety, correctness, reproducibility, and dependence of the output on the input/prompt and environment.",
    "Specifically, for correctness, we followed the taxonomy of Currie et al.",
    "to classify incorrect outputs more precisely into illusions, delusions, delirium, confabulation, and extrapolation, thus proposing a framework for a more precise and structured error classification to improve the characterization of incorrect outputs and enabling more detailed performance comparisons with other research."
  ]
}